        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Checks if a point is already inserted in the <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput> vector with a certain tolerance <computeroutput>eps_L2_squared</computeroutput>. Fills both the <computeroutput>X_near</computeroutput> vector with the points that within a ball of radius <computeroutput>sqrt(delta_R_squared)</computeroutput> centered at <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput> and the <computeroutput>closest_point</computeroutput> in <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput> wrt to <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput> if <computeroutput>fill_fn_params</computeroutput> is set to <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>samples</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>coord</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The point to check if it is already inserted in <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>X_near</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>When the function returns <computeroutput>false</computeroutput>, it contains the points in <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput> within <computeroutput>delta_R</computeroutput> centered at <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput> if <computeroutput>fill_fn_params</computeroutput> is set to <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>; otherwise, it is undefined. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>closest_point</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>When the function returns <computeroutput>false</computeroutput>, it contains the closest point in <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput> to <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput> if <computeroutput>fill_fn_params</computeroutput> is set to <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>; otherwise, it is undefined. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fill_fn_params</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>eps_L2_squared</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Squared Euclidean distance tolerance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>delta_R_squared</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Squared radius of the ball centered at <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><computeroutput>true</computeroutput> if <computeroutput>coord</computeroutput> is too close to any point in <computeroutput>samples</computeroutput> with a tolerance of <computeroutput>eps_L2_squared</computeroutput>; otherwise, <computeroutput>false</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
